The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Metro Recommends

THE DVD

 (Landmark, Rs 595) l Peter Gabriel, the former Genesis frontman, pulls off 

a brilliant mix of sound, visual and theatrics. Besides new songs, there are classics 

like Sledgehammer, Shaking the tree and Kiss that frog performed 

live. 

THE ADDA

 (December 19, Coffee House, 2 pm to 4 pm) l The original adda stop, College 

Street Coffee House, will come alive on Sunday afternoon with a clutch of Calcuttans 

? resident and non-resident ? engaging in two hours of jukti, tokko, 

goppo. The topic of discussion shall be the Resurgence of Calcutta, the 

moderator Shiloo Chattopadhyay, the participants Abhijit Banerjee, Maitresh Ghatak, 

Pramita Mullick, Moti Nandi, Joy Goswami, Anita Agnihotri and Indranil Dasgupta. 

THE EVENT

 (St. Xavier?s College grounds, December 23)

 l The borders blur as Strings from Pakistan shares the stage with Sophie and Shibani from India. Be there for the concert presented by the Xavier?s Alumni Association in association with The Telegraph and Eveready. 




